result.name: Curry King Indian Restaurant

reviews.text: This restaurant really saved our Indian group for three days! Although there is only one complaint about the curd they use, not good! Keep that aside, food tastes great! We couldn’t find any proper vegetarian food there! First we went to restaurant named BOMBAY KITCHEN, but it way too expensive that we had to find another restaurant. Finally we come here at night, and for all the nights in HK we had our dinner here. Good music, environment!

No air-conditioning when I visited. prices are on high side and service is nothing to rave about. Quality of food just above poor. Nothing special.

Was told by a friend that this restaurant had radically improved, so I decide to visit on the 12th July, 2019 and was presently surprised. ordered a chicken kebab, Jafrezi Prawn and Pulao rice. The food was very good. Pricing is still on the high side. Service was very good.

Fully crowded one. It's small but nice. Cost reasonable compared to other hotels. Indian food taste as like Indian food here. I could see many foreign visitors in this hotel. Should visit if you are staying in kowloon city.
Small cosy and good quality Indian restaurant. Always busy. Book ahead. Good curries and vegetable dishes. Strong range of Indian beer.

Definitely one of best authentic curries in town and worthy of it's name.  Has been around since forever and still good value for money!  You know an indian curry is good when indians dine there too! highly recommended
